    "body": "... by providing basic `__annotate__` implementation.\r\n\r\nFixes #7675.\r\n\r\nThe issue is that in 3.14, `wraps` reassigns `__annotate__` rather than `__annotations__`. The basic implementation I provide is a function that just returns the `__annotations__` dictionary (stored at the time it was created),\r\nwhile setting `__annotate__` just calls the function and then sets the `__annotations__` to the result. This should also stand a decent chance of working with non-cyfunctions.\r\n\r\nMy view is that `wraps` working correctly is a desirable property and should be tested.",
    "closed_at": null,
